\par \tab The funeral that followed was farce and tragedy. We attended the wrong casket and were shocked to be confronted by the visage of a young man, as if death had done my father good. Meanwhile, another family with a closed casket had buried our father.

\par \tab \'93Death suited him.\'94 It didn\rquote t matter that it wasn\rquote t true\emdash it seemed true. That he had gone into death old and come back young. And more comforting still\emdash the idea that there had been a mistake and he was aliv
e somewhere.
