he man, but \'93also irritated me intensely; I had the feeling he knew something I did not, something I wanted to know.\'94
\par \tab They remained in those positions, respectively sitting and standing, for over five minutes. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Duncan{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} somehow sensed that just as he should 
not sit down, he also should not speak. \'93I began to think this man held some power over me, and it was only later that I realized something in his eyes reminded me of Dad.\'94
\par \tab When Gaudy finally lifted his bespectacled face to stare at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Duncan{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, the flames reflected in the glass, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Duncan{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} saw an expression of absolute peace on the man\rquote s face. Relieved, he again moved to sit down, only to again be told, through a gesture, to remain standing.
