\par \tab He scooped up the starfish, held it in his hands. It lay there as contentedly as if in a tidal pool. \'93I don\rquote t expect anything, Janice,\'94 he said, each word carefully weighed, wrapped, tied with string before leaving his mouth. \'93
I have no one else to tell. No one else who saw me the last time. No one else who might possibly believe anything I saw. Starfish or no starfish.\'94
\par \tab \'93Tell Mom then. Mom would listen. If you speak softly enough, Dad might even pick up a whisper of it. Did you meet him down there?\'94
\par \tab He winced, sat back against the wall, next to a leering portrait by a painter named Sonter. The shadows and the sheen of black dust on his skin rendered him almost invisible.
\par \tab Coated by the darkness, he said, \'93I\rquote m sorry. I didn\rquote t mean to\emdash I didn\rquote t realize\'85But you know, Janice, you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\insrsid9058111\charrsid6828570 are}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\insrsid9058111\charrsid6828570  the only one who won\rquote t think me crazy.\'94
\par \tab The starfish had begun to explore the crook of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Duncan{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}\rquote s
 arm. Its rejuvenated cilia shone wetly, a thousand minute moving jewels amongst the windless reeds of his arm hairs.
\par \tab \'93It\rquote s so hard,\'94 he said. \'93Half of what you see seems like a hallucination, or a dream, even while you\rquote re living it. You are so unsure about what\rquote s real that you take all kinds of stupid risks. As if it can\rquote 
t hurt you. You float along, like a spore. You sit for days in caverns as large as cities, let the fungi creep up and devour you. The stars that can\rquote t be stars fall in on you in waves. An
d you just sit there. An afternoon in the park. A picnic for one.
\par \tab \'93}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\insrsid9058111\charrsid6828570 Things}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\insrsid9058111\charrsid6828570  walk by you. Some stop and stare. Some poke you or hit you, and then you have to pretend 
{\*\atrfstart 108113579}it is }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs24\v\insrsid12138243\charrsid6828570 {\*\atrfend 108113579}{\*\atnid LG}{\*\atnauthor Liz Gorinsky}\chatn {\*\annotation{\*\atnref 108113579}{\*\atndate -963149359}\ltrpar \pard\plain \ltrpar
