\par I found the standing still worse than the walking and running. I could disguise myself from the gray caps, but not from their servants\emdash the spores, the parasites, the tiny mushrooms caps, fungi, and lichen. They found me and infiltrated me\emdash 
I could feel their tendrils, their fleshy-dry-cold-warm pseudopods and cilia and strands slowly sliding up my skin, like a hundred tiny hands. They tried to remake me in their image}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\insrsid10122328\charrsid6828570 
