\par This entry about a defective \'93machine\'94 built by the gray caps is the strangest part of my brother\rquote s journal. By far. In its pure physicality I sense a level of discomfort rare for {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Duncan{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. More than a w
hiff of fear. As if, from fretful tossing and turning, he woke, reached for pen and notepad from the nightstand, and wrote down his first impressions of a fading nightmare. He appears at first anxious to record the experience, and then less so, the use of
 second person intended, I think, to place the burden of memory on the reader, to purge the images from his head. (It is more that I could not find words to accurately }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\insrsid7501382\charrsid6828570 convey }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\insrsid9058111\charrsid6828570 what I saw, and so I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\insrsid10122328\charrsid6828570 tried to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\insrsid7501382\charrsid6828570 describe}{\rtlch\fcs1 
