\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\insrsid9058111\charrsid6828570 Every human
 being is a puppet on strings, but the puppet half controls the strings, and the strings do not ascend to some anonymous Maker, but are glistening silver strands that connect one puppet to another. Each strand is sensitive to the vibrations of every other
 strand. Every vibration sings in not only the puppet\rquote s heart, but in the hearts of many other puppets, so that if you listen carefully, you can hear a low hum as of many hearts singing together\'85
When a strand snaps, when it breaks for love, or lack of love, or from hatred, or from pain\'85every other connected strand feels it, and every other connected heart feels it\emdash 
and since every strand and every heart are, in theory, connected, even if at their most distant limits, this means the effect is universal. All th
rough the darkness where shining strings are the only light, a woundedness occurs. And this hurt affects each strand and each puppet in a different way, because we are all puppets on strings and we all hurt and are hurt. And all the strings shimmer on reg
ardless, and all of our actions, no matter how small, have consequences to other puppets\'85
After we are dead, gone to join the darkness between the lines of light, the strands we leave behind still quiver their lost messages into the hearts of those other pup
pets we met along the way, on our journey from light into not-light. These lost strands are the memories we leave behind\'85
Magnify this effect by 25,000 souls and perhaps you can see why I cannot so lightly dismiss what you call a mistake. Each extinguished life leaves a hole in many other lives\emdash 
a series of small extinguishments that can never be completely forgotten or survived. Each survivor carries a little of the void within them as a result.
