imblytod Tribes, he had an affinity for tree climbing that no one could match, and a cut-bark scent that clung to him as if it was his birthright. His only pride revolved around his knowledge of the streets, and his well-tended, lightweight boots, which h
ad been given to him by his tribe when he had left for the city. He couldn\rquote t have been more than eighteen years old when I met him for the first time.
