air, listened to the distant cry of a hawk, and tried to hear the rustlings of mice and rabbits in the underbrush. We were already more than half a mile from our house.
\par \tab {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Duncan{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} peered into the forest\rquote s depths.
\par \tab \'93We need to go farther,\'94 he said.
\par \tab B
ack then, he was a thin little kid, small for his age, his shocking blonde hair beginning to turn brown. His bright blue eyes sometimes seemed too large for his face. He liked to wear long green shirts with brown shorts and sandals. He said it served as a
 kind of camouflage. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\cf0\revised\revauth1\revdttm110566619\insrsid11351199\charrsid6828570 (Camouflage or comfort\emdash I don\rquote t remember.) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs24\v\insrsid11351199\charrsid6828570 
