{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Duncan{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} at some point later in the writing process? My chronology is fuzzy.}}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\insrsid9058111\charrsid6828570 
, because I became accustomed to the deep forest that day. (It\rquote s more intense underground, Janice, because you can\rquote t match what you\rquote re seeing to anything you\rquote ve experienced before.)
\par \tab \'93Trust me,\'94 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Duncan{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} said, and grinned. He headed off again, at such a speed that I again had no choice but to follow him. In the shadows}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\insrsid12067414\charrsid6828570 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\insrsid9058111\charrsid6828570  my brother\rquote s thin, wiry frame resembled more the thick, muscular body of a man. Was there any point at which 
I could convince him to stop}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\insrsid12067414\charrsid6828570 , or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \deleted\f39\revauthdel1\revdttmdel110566632\insrsid12067414\delrsid5181854\charrsid6828570 he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\insrsid12067414\charrsid6828570 would }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\cf0\revised\revauth1\revdttm110566632\insrsid5181854\charrsid6828570 he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\insrsid15732085\charrsid6828570 stop}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
