t take it. Nothing affected me like that. Not the underground. Not the disease taking over my body. But you, crumpled in the bathtub, half-dead. You looked as though, without ever going underground, you had suffered all the terrors to be found there.)

\par So you can imagine my amusement over the doctor\rquote s concern about my thumb prick. The pricks should have been more concerned about where I found the pen\emdash and where they had made me stay, and whose company I\rquote d been keeping.
