\par The hallways were like corridors to bad dreams. They rambled this way and that with no order, no coherence. You might find your destination, or you might not. It all depended on luc
k. I remember that once I turned a corner, and there was a dandelion growing out of a clump of dirt on the floor. After that, I wouldn\rquote 
t have been surprised if the lower levels were vast swamps or brambles, through which inmates thrashed their way to open space. Once, I swear I even saw a gray cap}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\insrsid9570535\charrsid6828570  in the distance}{
