\par Edward only talked to me in chirps and whistles, and the occasional drawing. He always drew tunnels\emdash crisscrossing tunnels, honeycombing tunnels, tunnels without end. He used black chalk or charcoal on butcher paper. That was all we had in there
 to chart our creativity.
\par \'93I know,\'94 I told him. \'93I know. You just want to go underground. Like my brother. My brother\rquote s been underground. Trust me. You don\rquote t want to go there.\'94
