\par One day, on an impulse, I silenced his chirping with a hug. I held him
 tight, and I could feel his body shudder, relax, and melt into that embrace. I heard him whisper a word or two. I could not understand the words, but they were human. He did not want to let go. Something inside of him didn\rquote 
t believe in his own insanity. And suddenly, I found myself holding him tighter, and crying, and not believing in my insanity, either.
